senses.sense: The 10<sup>th</sup> letter of the English alphabet, called jay and written in the Latin script.
(slang) A term for a marijuana cigarette ('joint').
examples: "I went outside to smoke myself a J" — Paul Simon, from the song "Late in the Evening" from the album, "One Trick Pony."

senses.sense: (mathematics) An alternative version of i, the positive square root of -1; used in the context of electronics.
(mathematics) The second unit vector, after i
(stenoscript) a suffix or final syllable /ʃən/ (-tion, -sion, etc.)
